  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this study is to confirm the sensitivity of a stool DNA test for detection
      of colorectal cancer and pre-cancer.

      Another objective is to provide anonymous, clinically characterized specimens for a
      bio-repository for future colorectal cancer-related test development.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients who have been recently diagnosed with colo-rectal cancer or pre-cancer will be asked
      to submit a stool sample(s)(at least 7 days AFTER colonoscopy) and will have the option of
      submitting blood and tissue samples for future colo-rectal cancer-related test development.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
